<subSubSection pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="54.[151,1436,1974,2034]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,260,1975,1999]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Remarks</emphasis>
. Currently, there are 
<number box="[503,531,1974,1998]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="62.0">62</number>
species of 
<taxonomicName box="[660,738,1974,1998]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Stilpon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[660,738,1974,1998]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Stilpon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
worldwide (including two species described here). However, only two species have been reported from the Afrotropical Region: 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith, 1969" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1969" box="[929,1183,2010,2034]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Stilpon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leleupi">
<emphasis box="[929,1035,2010,2034]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">S. leleupi</emphasis>
Smith, 
<number box="[1127,1183,2010,2034]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="1969.0">1969</number>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1199,1349,2010,2034]" name="South Africa" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">South Africa</collectingCountry>
) and 
<emphasis box="[1415,1436,2011,2034]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">S.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
